CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 9, 1960, pg.13 reads: "$26 Million for URA - David Walker (third from left), commissioner of the Urban Renewal Administration (URA), announced Tuesday night that URA has approved Federal cash grants totaling $26 million for the East Liberty urban renewal area. East Liberty leaders hearing the report at a Hotel Webster Hall dinner of the East Liberty Chamber of Commerce were, left to right: Stanley Hahn, new president of the East Liberty Chamber of Commerce; John E. Hale, retiring president, and Herbert C. Mansmann, president of the East Liberty Citizens Renewal Council. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of left to right: Stanley Hahn, John E. Hale, David Walker, and Herbert C. Mansmann, gathered for East Liberty Chamber of Commerce dinner in Webster Hall
